  "prompt": "How do I treat a crooked smile?",
  "response": "Treating a crooked smile depends on the underlying cause. Here are some common approaches:\n\n### 1. **Orthodontic Treatment**\n   - **Braces**: Traditional metal braces or ceramic braces can straighten misaligned teeth.\n   - **Clear Aligners**: Options like Invisalign are a less noticeable alternative to braces.\n   - **Retainers**: Used after braces or aligners to maintain alignment.\n\n### 2. **Dental Work**\n   - **Veneers**: Thin porcelain shells placed over teeth to improve their appearance.\n   - **Bonding**: Using composite resin to reshape or cover imperfections.\n   - **Crowns**: Caps placed over damaged or misaligned teeth.\n   - **Tooth Contouring**: Reshaping teeth to improve alignment or symmetry.\n\n### 3. **Orthognathic Surgery**\n   - If the crooked smile is due to jaw misalignment, corrective surgery may be needed.\n\n### 4. **Botulinum Toxin (Botox)**\n   - For a crooked smile caused by muscle asymmetry, Botox can relax overactive facial muscles to create balance.\n\n### 5. **Physical Therapy or Exercises**\n   - Facial muscle exercises can sometimes help improve symmetry in mild cases.\n\n### 6. **Treat Underlying Causes**\n   - If the crooked smile is due to injury, nerve damage, or a medical condition (like Bell\u2019s palsy or stroke), treating the root cause is essential.\n\n### 7. **Cosmetic Solutions**\n   - Lip fillers or other cosmetic procedures can help enhance symmetry.\n\n### Steps to Take:\n   - Consult a **dentist** or **orthodontist** to determine the cause of your crooked smile.\n   - For muscle-related asymmetry, see a **maxillofacial surgeon** or **cosmetic specialist**.\n   - Follow a personalized treatment plan based on your diagnosis.\n\nThe best approach will depend on the severity and cause of your crooked smile, so professional evaluation is key.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
